{{page-title "Documentation — Summaries"}}
<div class="container mx-auto max-w-3xl py-6 px-4 space-y-6">

  <Panel::Card>
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-3">Summaries</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Summaries are AI-generated executive summaries tailored to a specific job
      post. They're typically 2–4 sentences that open your resume or cover
      letter — replacing the generic "10+ years of experience in..." objective
      statement with something that speaks directly to what the employer is
      looking for.
    </p>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of a generated summary" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">When to Use Summaries</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600 text-sm list-disc list-inside">
      <li><strong>Resume opener</strong>
        — replace your static objective statement with one tailored to the
        specific role</li>
      <li><strong>Cover letter intro</strong>
        — use as the first paragraph to anchor the letter to the role</li>
      <li><strong>LinkedIn "About" section</strong>
        — generate a few options and pick the best phrasing</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-3">
      One summary per application keeps them specific and relevant. Generic
      summaries are easy to spot and undermine your application.
    </p>
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">How Generation Works</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      From a Job Post detail page, click "Generate Summary." The AI reads the
      job description and your Career Data and writes a concise positioning
      statement that highlights the parts of your background most relevant to
      the role. Edit it until it sounds exactly right.
    </p>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of the summary generation interface" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

  <Panel::Card>
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Example Summary</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs italic mb-3">Generated for: Senior
      Full-Stack Engineer at Acme Corp</p>
    <div
      class="bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200 rounded p-4 text-sm text-gray-700"
    >
      <p>
        Backend engineer with 8 years building high-traffic Python/Django
        services, including a patient intake API serving 200k requests daily at
        Meridian Health. Strong record of end-to-end ownership — from
        architecture decisions through production ops — with meaningful
        experience on Ember.js frontends. Drawn to Acme's platform team because
        the technical surface maps closely to where I've done my best work.
      </p>
    </div>
    {{! <img src="" alt="screenshot of this example summary in the show view" /> }}
  </Panel::Card>

</div>